This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it focuses on coreference resolution, which is a key task in NLP. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG) to evaluate gender bias in these systems. The study also involves analyzing real-world and textual gender statistics, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). However, given the focus on language and machine learning, we believe that cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) is less likely to be a relevant sub-category.
